AS BRITAIN approaches a European election it had expected to avoid, we examine how the Brexit mess is dissolving party allegiances. Turkey was once praised for the way it treated Syrians fleeing conflict, but that welcome is wearing thin as war has dragged on. Also, kinky and camp meet fraught politics in this year’s Eurovision Song Contest. Runtime: 21min    Listen on: Apple Podcasts | Spotify | Google | Stitcher | TuneIn